00:23:14.890 --> 00:23:18.250
[People in the world
aren't that interested in you!]

00:23:18.720 --> 00:23:20.450
[If they're not interested,
why are you calling me then?]

00:23:20.580 --> 00:23:21.490
-Kwanghee.
-Yeah?

00:23:21.490 --> 00:23:23.030
I want to ask you something.

00:23:23.030 --> 00:23:25.590
[Are you close with Jung Hae-in?]

00:23:25.760 --> 00:23:26.280
We keep in touch occasionally.

00:23:26.280 --> 00:23:27.440
[Carefully bringing up the real topic]

00:23:27.440 --> 00:23:29.640
-You contact Hae-in sometimes?
-Yeah.

00:23:29.980 --> 00:23:31.910
[Hong Jinkyung: Besides liking alcohol,
what else does Hae-in like?][Sis…]

00:23:31.910 --> 00:23:33.130
Food-wise.

00:23:33.690 --> 00:23:34.670
-Sis?
-What?

00:23:35.350 --> 00:23:37.970
[You complained about my phone settings
and said you wanted to call,]

00:23:37.970 --> 00:23:40.600
[but you're only asking
about Jung Hae-in!]

00:23:41.310 --> 00:23:44.620
[Well, you're close with him,
so I need to make him something.]

00:23:46.250 --> 00:23:47.320
[Are you filming a YouTube show?]

00:23:47.670 --> 00:23:49.700
[PD Taeho has a program…]

00:23:49.700 --> 00:23:50.080
We're filming now.

00:23:50.080 --> 00:23:52.410
-Taeho's production company?
-Yeah.

00:23:52.410 --> 00:23:53.670
[So how close are you two really?]
[Let's do it together!]

00:23:53.670 --> 00:23:54.750
[Let's do it together!
Let's do it together!]

00:23:54.750 --> 00:23:56.710
Do what together?

00:23:56.790 --> 00:23:59.060
[Sis, I'm free today.
Should I just go to Insadong?]

00:23:59.060 --> 00:24:00.980
[I'm great at greetings.
I greet idols all the time.]

00:24:01.180 --> 00:24:01.420
Jung Hae-in sent me
holiday wishes not long ago.

00:24:01.420 --> 00:24:05.370
[Overstating the connection
as soon as it's for a show]

00:24:05.570 --> 00:24:07.270
[I had a meal with Hae-in before…]

00:24:07.270 --> 00:24:08.030
-He likes good food.
-Really?

00:24:08.030 --> 00:24:10.810
[Hae-in loves good food!]

00:24:10.890 --> 00:24:11.310
-What?
-He likes delicious food.

00:24:11.310 --> 00:24:12.170
[What? Finally got intel on the Manito!]

00:24:12.170 --> 00:24:12.870
What does he like?

00:24:12.870 --> 00:24:14.390
When we ate together,

00:24:14.700 --> 00:24:17.050
[it was Japanese food, a set menu.]

00:24:17.050 --> 00:24:18.610
Very neat and tidy.

00:24:18.730 --> 00:24:19.480
-He also likes drinking.
-Was it kaiseki?

00:24:19.480 --> 00:24:21.430
[Japanese course meal—was it kaiseki?]

00:24:21.490 --> 00:24:22.710
[Are you scolding me now?
(Sounds like a swear word)]

00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:25.070
I meant kaiseki—
Japanese home-style cuisine.

00:24:25.070 --> 00:24:25.190
-Home-style has that name too?
-I guess so.

00:24:25.190 --> 00:24:27.540
[Home-style has that name too?]

00:24:27.850 --> 00:24:30.410
[Maybe not kaiseki(?)]

00:24:30.410 --> 00:24:32.190
I don't know. I don't know those things.

00:24:32.190 --> 00:24:32.910
Are you hosting this show by yourself?

00:24:32.910 --> 00:24:35.010
[Kwanghee's curiosity suddenly explodes]

00:24:35.010 --> 00:24:37.490
And then you go meet celebrities?

00:24:37.860 --> 00:24:41.340
[It's not just me! It's Manito.]

00:24:41.390 --> 00:24:45.690
[Oh my gosh, you got on that show?
Weren't there only 5 cast members?]

00:24:45.690 --> 00:24:47.910
[Is PD Kim Taeho being unfair?
I'm in the same company as Choo Sunghoon.]

00:24:47.910 --> 00:24:50.140
[How could he not contact me?]

00:24:50.140 --> 00:24:53.060
[Did they invite you to Manito?
I was wondering why they didn't call me.]

00:24:53.060 --> 00:24:55.500
[Since Infinite Challenge,
the director hasn't contacted me once…]

00:24:55.500 --> 00:24:57.950
[I mention him everywhere I go.]

00:24:57.950 --> 00:24:57.960
[My ears are about to bleed…]

00:24:57.960 --> 00:24:59.900
I need to hang up.

00:25:00.010 --> 00:25:01.140
Sis, PD Kim Taeho...

00:25:01.350 --> 00:25:02.880
[Make PD Kim Taeho
take responsibility for me!]

00:25:03.130 --> 00:25:06.110
[Where are you?
Why can you shout like that? Haha]

00:25:06.120 --> 00:25:07.850
[If I ever switch sides, I'd say
I'm no longer on PD Kim Taeho’s team.]

00:25:07.850 --> 00:25:09.580
[From now on,
the complaints will never stop.]

00:25:09.580 --> 00:25:11.400
[People's hearts change in an instant.
Complaining nonstop]

00:25:11.400 --> 00:25:12.100
[Complaining nonstop]

00:25:12.100 --> 00:25:13.340
What's wrong?

00:25:13.510 --> 00:25:14.130
Did you start drinking
in the middle of the day?

00:25:14.130 --> 00:25:15.500
[Hard to believe you're sober]

00:25:15.500 --> 00:25:17.370
What would I drink in the daytime?

00:25:17.640 --> 00:25:19.650
Alright, Kwanghee.

00:25:19.700 --> 00:25:19.710
-Are you tired now?
-I'm exhausted.

00:25:19.710 --> 00:25:21.080
[Q. Are you tired now? Yes.]

00:25:21.080 --> 00:25:22.340
I'm going to hang up.

00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:23.530
I'm tired.

00:25:23.670 --> 00:25:25.370
[Alright, Kwanghee…]

00:25:25.370 --> 00:25:25.450
Take care.

00:25:25.450 --> 00:25:26.530
[Take care. Bye. Bye.]

00:25:26.530 --> 00:25:28.260
-Weren't you curious about Hae-in?
-Bye.

00:25:28.260 --> 00:25:29.990
-I still have more to say.
-Bye.

00:25:30.110 --> 00:25:31.010
Happy New Year.

00:25:31.010 --> 00:25:33.210
[Hangs up.]

00:25:34.080 --> 00:25:37.270
[Ugh I'm so tired!
He won't hang up.]

00:25:38.840 --> 00:25:40.660
[He's calling again. What do I do…]

00:25:41.020 --> 00:25:41.100
Should I answer? Forget it.

00:25:41.100 --> 00:25:42.880
[No courage to pick up]

00:25:42.880 --> 00:25:43.910
He'll just say the same things again.

00:25:43.910 --> 00:25:45.630
[Won't meet for a while.]

00:25:45.630 --> 00:25:46.300
Alright, let's leave it.

00:25:46.300 --> 00:25:50.060
[Let's not see each other for a while,
from Kwanghee…]

00:25:50.480 --> 00:25:51.670
[What's going on?]

00:25:51.910 --> 00:25:53.380
[Didn't Hyungdon just give me
Yim Siwan's number?]

00:25:53.380 --> 00:25:57.810
This is actress Im Soo-hyang.

00:25:57.810 --> 00:26:00.090
It's not Yim Siwan.

00:26:00.210 --> 00:26:00.370
I texted thinking
it was Yim Siwan's number.

00:26:00.370 --> 00:26:02.160
[Said to be Yim Siwan
but it's Im Soo-hyang…]

00:26:02.160 --> 00:26:04.830
Then she told me she's Im Soo-hyang.

00:26:05.240 --> 00:26:07.630
[To Actress Im Soo-hyang: Oh no,
there must be a mistake.]

00:26:07.630 --> 00:26:10.030
[Sorry. Happy New Year.]

00:26:10.420 --> 00:26:12.550
[Ah, Jung Hyungdon, what are you doing?]

00:26:13.340 --> 00:26:16.390
[I need to call him. This is insane.]

00:26:17.330 --> 00:26:18.560
[Calling the source of the chaos again]

00:26:18.560 --> 00:26:21.190
-Jinkyung.
-Hyungdon.

00:26:21.970 --> 00:26:24.580
[Hong Jinkyung: Didn't you give me
Yim Siwan's number?]

00:26:24.580 --> 00:26:25.290
[It was Soohyang!]

00:26:25.290 --> 00:26:26.950
I said Yim Siwan.

00:26:28.140 --> 00:26:29.960
[I said Yim Siwan…]

00:26:29.960 --> 00:26:31.620
So you gave me Im Soo-hyang's number?

00:26:31.620 --> 00:26:33.840
[Yim Si… you mean Im Soo-hyang.]

00:26:34.430 --> 00:26:37.270
[Do you know Yim Siwan's number?]
[Of course I know Soohyang's.]

00:26:37.370 --> 00:26:37.630
Then give me Yim Siwan's number.

00:26:37.630 --> 00:26:38.740
[(Yim Siwan 22)]

00:26:38.740 --> 00:26:39.050
-Okay, I'll send it.
-Okay, okay.

00:26:39.050 --> 00:26:40.080
[(Soohyang 22)]

00:26:40.080 --> 00:26:41.080
Okay, okay, okay.

00:26:41.170 --> 00:26:41.430
-OK.
-Send it to me.

00:26:41.430 --> 00:26:43.050
[Both have perfect pronunciation
yet still can't communicate…]

00:26:43.050 --> 00:26:43.840
Okay.

00:26:44.140 --> 00:26:45.660
[Hong Jinkyung:
So I thought it was Yim Siwan.]

00:26:45.660 --> 00:26:48.060
-I even told him I'm Hong Jinkyung.
-Oh, Siwan.

00:26:48.060 --> 00:26:49.710
[Frankly] [I misheard it as Im Soo-hyang!]

00:26:49.940 --> 00:26:54.890
[Are Im Soo-hyang and Jung Hae-in close?]
[I have no idea?]

00:26:55.330 --> 00:26:55.810
No, I was asking about Yim Siwan.

00:26:55.810 --> 00:26:58.630
[The more I think about it,
the more ridiculous it gets]

00:26:58.630 --> 00:27:01.140
What am I supposed to do with
Im Soo-hyang's number?

00:27:01.140 --> 00:27:02.780
[I don't even have Siwan's number.]

00:27:02.780 --> 00:27:04.400
-Really?
-Yeah.

00:27:05.190 --> 00:27:05.650
Really? Then go enjoy your game.

00:27:05.650 --> 00:27:07.270
[The call ends with nothing gained]

00:27:07.270 --> 00:27:08.930
-Okay.
-Bye.

00:27:09.250 --> 00:27:13.150
[Hong Jinkyung: I need to
edit my contacts… Im Soo-hyang…]

00:27:13.680 --> 00:27:16.230
[Meanwhile, Siwan's number
is still a mystery.]

00:27:16.560 --> 00:27:20.800
[Siwan's number…
Kwanghee might know, right?]

00:27:20.950 --> 00:27:21.390
-Sis.
-Kwanghee.

00:27:21.390 --> 00:27:22.980
[After going in circles,
back to Kwanghee.]

00:27:22.980 --> 00:27:26.040
Sis, what on earth happened?
Why do you keep calling me?

00:27:26.560 --> 00:27:28.820
[Give me Yim Siwan's number.]
[Are you sending Yim Siwan something?]

00:27:28.820 --> 00:27:31.140
Yim Siwan? Are you sending him something?

00:27:31.140 --> 00:27:32.450
[Macchiato? Wha… wha… what was it?]

00:27:32.450 --> 00:27:35.500
-What macchiato? It's Manito.
-You're giving him a gift?

00:27:35.500 --> 00:27:36.740
No.

00:27:36.880 --> 00:27:37.250
I want to ask Siwan
what Jung Hae-in likes.

00:27:37.250 --> 00:27:39.960
[Hong Jinkyung: I want to ask Siwan
what Jung Hae-in likes.]

00:27:39.960 --> 00:27:43.160
-Right, they eat together a lot.
-Yeah.

00:27:43.270 --> 00:27:43.300
[Then I'll send you Siwan's number.]

00:27:43.300 --> 00:27:46.040
-I'll send you his number.
-OK.

00:27:46.320 --> 00:27:48.020
[But no one's giving me anything?]

00:27:48.020 --> 00:27:49.730
[Sunghoon and I are
even in the same company.]

00:27:49.740 --> 00:27:50.450
No, no, no, it's all predetermined.

00:27:50.450 --> 00:27:51.940
[It's predetermined? The Manito pairing.]
[You can't lie to me, sis.]

00:27:51.940 --> 00:27:54.890
-The Manito pairing.
-Really? Don't lie to me.

00:27:55.020 --> 00:27:55.240
It really is predetermined.

00:27:55.240 --> 00:27:56.430
[The ear-blasting rant begins again]

00:27:56.430 --> 00:27:57.520
It was set from the start.

00:27:57.520 --> 00:28:00.800
[So the show… did the crew
exclude me again? Ugh, seriously.]

00:28:01.980 --> 00:28:03.720
[Wouldn't it be nice to appear
on TV after a long time?]

00:28:03.720 --> 00:28:04.830
[If I popped up again,
wouldn't that be refreshing?]

00:28:04.830 --> 00:28:05.560
Kwanghee.

00:28:05.700 --> 00:28:05.730
-Kwanghee.
-Yeah.

00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:07.440
[Kwanghee, hang up.]

00:28:07.440 --> 00:28:08.420
Hang up.

00:28:08.750 --> 00:28:10.480
[Sincerely: Sis, can I say
something to the viewers?]

00:28:10.480 --> 00:28:11.810
Yeah, go ahead.

00:28:11.830 --> 00:28:15.620
[For the upcoming 20… ah, 2026 —
Happy New Year, everyone.]

00:28:16.750 --> 00:28:18.900
[Wishing you health
and happiness every day.]

00:28:19.290 --> 00:28:19.330
[Her ears exhausted from gathering
info about Manito Hae-in]

00:28:19.330 --> 00:28:20.640
Alright then.

00:28:22.740 --> 00:28:25.700
[Hae-in sets off to
carry out the Manito mission.]

00:28:25.700 --> 00:28:27.170
It's freezing.

00:28:27.270 --> 00:28:28.390
[Jung Hae-in: Oh! Wait.]

00:28:28.390 --> 00:28:30.770
[Jung Hae-in: I can just buy chips
and gummies here, right?]

00:28:30.770 --> 00:28:32.590
Buy them at the convenience store.

00:28:32.590 --> 00:28:34.120
[Thinking]

00:28:34.290 --> 00:28:37.400
[But before that…
Operation name: Super Express Delivery.]

00:28:37.560 --> 00:28:37.590
[A new plan formed in just 10 seconds]

00:28:37.590 --> 00:28:40.240
I need a helmet to cover my face.

00:28:40.380 --> 00:28:43.880
[Go buy a helmet… but before that!]

00:28:44.070 --> 00:28:45.490
[Oh right, I need to buy gummies.]

00:28:45.490 --> 00:28:47.330
[No, helmet first.]

00:28:47.330 --> 00:28:48.530
So the store doesn't close.

00:28:48.530 --> 00:28:51.190
[I'm such an extreme P-type…]

00:28:51.630 --> 00:28:55.460
[This is unbelievable! Now I'm actually
planning decisively like this(?)]

00:28:56.080 --> 00:28:56.850
[A structured me — impressive]

00:28:56.850 --> 00:28:57.900
Seriously.

00:28:58.130 --> 00:28:59.060
Hello.

00:28:59.220 --> 00:28:59.690
Hi, can I buy a motorcycle
helmet if I come now?

00:28:59.690 --> 00:29:02.440
[Proactive prep —
calling the shop in advance]

00:29:02.510 --> 00:29:04.450
[Which helmet are you looking for?
— Shop staff]

00:29:04.450 --> 00:29:05.100
[Which helmet
are you looking for? — Shop staff.]

00:29:05.100 --> 00:29:05.750
[Jung Hae-in: No specific model.]

00:29:06.090 --> 00:29:07.810
[Just one that covers
my face as much as possible.]

00:29:07.810 --> 00:29:10.740
Like the kind delivery riders use.

00:29:10.770 --> 00:29:13.320
[Shop staff: We have three-quarter helmets
and full-face helmets.]

00:29:13.320 --> 00:29:15.170
[Jung Hae-in: Okay,
I'll come take a look.]

00:29:15.530 --> 00:29:15.910
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:29:15.910 --> 00:29:19.230
[A very "planner-like" call
with little actual outcome]

00:29:20.230 --> 00:29:22.270
[Jung Hae-in:
I don't get motion sickness.]

00:29:22.950 --> 00:29:25.070
[Self-promo: I'm a great driver.]

00:29:25.170 --> 00:29:25.860
I'll be there soon.

00:29:25.860 --> 00:29:26.820
[Safe and comfy — Super Express Delivery
1988-0401.]

00:29:26.820 --> 00:29:28.320
About 10 minutes.

00:29:30.200 --> 00:29:33.010
[Jung Hae-in: But right now it feels very…
how should I say…]

00:29:33.390 --> 00:29:34.890
[A very free-form variety show?]

00:29:35.020 --> 00:29:36.430
[For someone like me,
it feels quite spontaneous…]

00:29:36.520 --> 00:29:36.570
[Spontaneous me is very satisfied]

00:29:36.570 --> 00:29:38.630
I really like this approach.

00:29:39.030 --> 00:29:41.140
[But how do I…]

00:29:41.380 --> 00:29:44.300
[Jung Hae-in: Since I'm…
not a very funny person…]

00:29:44.300 --> 00:29:47.310
[Jung Hae-in: I worry about how they'll
edit it to be interesting.]

00:29:47.590 --> 00:29:51.000
[If it's weird, just cut it out.
If it's boring...]

00:29:52.050 --> 00:29:53.930
[so people won't change the channel.]

00:29:54.270 --> 00:29:54.810
So far, it's going pretty smoothly.

00:29:54.810 --> 00:29:57.250
[Safe and comfy — Super Express Delivery
1988-0401]

00:29:57.920 --> 00:29:58.870
[Arrives at the motorcycle shop]

00:29:58.870 --> 00:30:00.110
Hello.

00:30:00.300 --> 00:30:00.340
[I'm here to buy a helmet.]

00:30:00.340 --> 00:30:02.430
-I'm here to buy a helmet.
-Sure.

00:30:02.620 --> 00:30:05.090
[Jung Hae-in: Sir,
for something like this…]

00:30:05.370 --> 00:30:07.010
[A sealed one —
can I add a bit of color? OK.]

00:30:07.010 --> 00:30:07.990
Yes.

00:30:08.120 --> 00:30:08.600
Replace the sealed part
with a different color.

00:30:08.600 --> 00:30:10.060
[Plan: customize it
so I'm completely unrecognizable.]

00:30:10.060 --> 00:30:11.330
Then you wouldn't be able
to see my face at all, right?

00:30:11.330 --> 00:30:12.980
You could say it's totally hidden.

00:30:12.980 --> 00:30:13.420
[Ding-ding]

00:30:13.420 --> 00:30:14.180
In that case,

00:30:14.180 --> 00:30:16.440
[Perfect! With inner face protection
and built-in tinted visor]

00:30:16.440 --> 00:30:17.430
Others can't see your eyes.

00:30:17.430 --> 00:30:17.650
Then this one should be dark too.

00:30:17.650 --> 00:30:18.890
[That fits perfectly, right?]

00:30:18.890 --> 00:30:20.300
So the eyes won't be visible either.

00:30:20.300 --> 00:30:21.970
[Decision made immediately.
Let me try it on.]

00:30:21.970 --> 00:30:22.800
[With this on, I could walk
right up to my Manito]

00:30:22.800 --> 00:30:23.250
[and no one would know]

00:30:23.250 --> 00:30:24.160
I'm your Manito.

00:30:24.160 --> 00:30:25.240
[Full of confidence]

00:30:25.240 --> 00:30:27.320
Drop off the gift and just walk away.

00:30:27.430 --> 00:30:27.950
What could they even do to me?

00:30:27.950 --> 00:30:29.760
[They can't exactly
take my helmet off.]

00:30:30.280 --> 00:30:32.440
[They probably won't recognize me, right?]

00:30:32.830 --> 00:30:35.020
[Voice change: Hello, I'm your Manito.]

00:30:35.130 --> 00:30:36.530
[You don't recognize me, right?]

00:30:36.730 --> 00:30:38.910
[Over-immersed] [Sir, do you have
this in a darker shade?]

00:30:39.030 --> 00:30:40.020
Lower my voice a bit more.
[Perfect]

00:30:40.020 --> 00:30:41.540
Then I just need a neck warmer.

00:30:41.540 --> 00:30:42.730
[Go just like this]

00:30:42.770 --> 00:30:42.920
[I'll say I'm the Manito, hand
over the gift, and that's it.]

00:30:42.920 --> 00:30:44.250
Just say I'm the Manito.

00:30:44.260 --> 00:30:45.190
[Invincible helmet]

00:30:45.280 --> 00:30:45.420
Then turn around and run.

00:30:45.420 --> 00:30:46.840
[And run away]

00:30:46.840 --> 00:30:48.080
Run.

00:30:48.890 --> 00:30:49.370
[Suddenly pulls out a recommended item]

00:30:49.370 --> 00:30:50.740
We also have this one. Do you need this?

00:30:50.740 --> 00:30:51.100
This is perfect.

00:30:51.100 --> 00:30:53.520
[As if by fate —
the owner's delivery vest]

00:30:53.520 --> 00:30:53.850
Wear something like this too.

00:30:53.850 --> 00:30:55.890
[Immediately takes off jacket]
[Sir, you're the best!]

00:30:56.020 --> 00:30:56.350
Put on this kind of outfit.

00:30:56.350 --> 00:30:58.250
[Super excited]

00:30:58.310 --> 00:30:58.400
Now I look like a pro,
like a delivery rider.

00:30:58.400 --> 00:31:00.060
[Jung Hae-in:
With the vest on, I look like a pro.]

00:31:00.060 --> 00:31:01.720
[Like a delivery rider.]

00:31:02.540 --> 00:31:02.770
Right, I definitely need this vest.

00:31:02.770 --> 00:31:05.040
[Extremely satisfied]

00:31:05.980 --> 00:31:07.140
[But this…]

00:31:07.140 --> 00:31:08.630
Is this yours, sir?

00:31:09.230 --> 00:31:10.400
[Is it vintage?]

00:31:10.850 --> 00:31:10.930
[The worn-in look makes it feel more authentic.
I even see a pen in it]

00:31:10.930 --> 00:31:12.870
It's vintage, with a bit of wear.

00:31:13.000 --> 00:31:14.710
I even see a pen in it.

00:31:14.710 --> 00:31:15.070
[The worn look actually
boosts the disguise]

00:31:15.070 --> 00:31:16.720
This is amazing.

00:31:17.330 --> 00:31:19.280
Then I'll take these two.

00:31:19.650 --> 00:31:20.840
That's it.

00:31:21.010 --> 00:31:22.410
[Perfect]

00:31:22.600 --> 00:31:22.720
This should keep me from being exposed.

00:31:22.720 --> 00:31:25.610
[Super Express Delivery disguise
purchase complete!]

00:31:25.840 --> 00:31:26.020
[Enters a convenience store
to buy snacks and gummies]

00:31:26.020 --> 00:31:28.130
There should be chips.

00:31:31.650 --> 00:31:33.440
[Why aren't there any gummies?]

00:31:33.690 --> 00:31:35.560
[Jung Hae-in: I'll buy snacks here first.]

00:31:35.560 --> 00:31:37.410
[Jung Hae-in: I'll have to go
somewhere else for gummies.]

00:31:37.710 --> 00:31:38.000
[Hae-in's plan keeps
changing every minute]

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:40.110
How many should I get… hold on.

00:31:41.770 --> 00:31:45.730
[Five… probably not enough.]

00:31:46.090 --> 00:31:48.670
[Could you give me more chips…?]
[You want all the stock?]

00:31:48.670 --> 00:31:50.460
[Twelve packs total.][Okay!]

00:31:50.690 --> 00:31:52.490
[Jung Hae-in: Okay,
this should be enough.]

00:31:52.620 --> 00:31:53.840
[Actually…]

00:31:53.990 --> 00:31:54.060
[Just buy the whole box.]

00:31:54.060 --> 00:31:56.370
I'll just take them in the box.

00:31:56.370 --> 00:31:58.830
[So 17 packs in total?]
[Yes!]

00:32:00.420 --> 00:32:02.920
[A full box]

00:32:03.910 --> 00:32:05.420
Alright, next.

00:32:05.670 --> 00:32:08.230
[So far… going perfectly]

00:32:08.530 --> 00:32:08.830
Everything's smooth.

00:32:08.830 --> 00:32:09.840
[Heads to a department store
to buy gummies]

00:32:09.840 --> 00:32:11.820
Still need gummies.

00:32:13.850 --> 00:32:15.340
[Bread-Myeongsoo Operation]

00:32:15.340 --> 00:32:16.090
[Yongsan charcoal-grilled bakery;
Mangwon-dong scoopable scone shop]

00:32:16.090 --> 00:32:16.840
[Mangwon-dong sea-salt bread shop;
Younjung sets off with a smooth plan.]

00:32:17.270 --> 00:32:20.700
[Phew… ready to go?]

00:32:21.430 --> 00:32:23.060
[haha]

00:32:23.400 --> 00:32:26.180
[haha — probably nervous laughter]

00:32:26.380 --> 00:32:28.910
[This is fun so far!
Right now it's… it's…]

00:32:29.170 --> 00:32:29.790
Because someone's sitting next to me.

00:32:29.790 --> 00:32:30.900
[Excited even though they're strangers]

00:32:30.900 --> 00:32:33.360
They're all people
I'm meeting for the first time.

00:32:33.360 --> 00:32:34.470
[But I—]

00:32:34.470 --> 00:32:37.210
[Go Younjung: When I'm with friends,
I'm very driven to be funny]

00:32:37.420 --> 00:32:39.480
[In other places, I get a bit shy…]

00:32:40.100 --> 00:32:43.180
[haha] [Self-promo: I'm actually
a very funny person]

00:32:43.510 --> 00:32:44.700
[Usually a total mischief-maker]

00:32:44.700 --> 00:32:44.900
It's so interesting.

00:32:44.900 --> 00:32:46.290
[Image / Footage / Info:
Go Younjung' socials]

00:32:46.610 --> 00:32:48.560
[The crew: We heard you were very nervous
during filming…]

00:32:48.560 --> 00:32:50.640
[I'm not nervous anymore!]

00:32:50.810 --> 00:32:51.770
[Younjung once nervous
at an awards ceremony]

00:32:51.770 --> 00:32:52.740
[that became a hot topic]

00:32:52.740 --> 00:32:55.250
[Haha] [Full of energy][I overcame it!]

00:32:55.320 --> 00:32:57.460
[Go Younjung: This time, because of
drama promotions,]

00:32:57.460 --> 00:33:00.710
[Go Younjung: we really
filmed for over ten hours, so…]

00:33:01.120 --> 00:33:02.190
[So easy]

00:33:02.190 --> 00:33:02.690
I'm free now.

00:33:02.690 --> 00:33:04.460
[After a crash course,
turning into a pro (?)]

00:33:05.140 --> 00:33:06.960
[Haha]

00:33:07.350 --> 00:33:09.390
[On the way to buy bread, full of smiles]

00:33:09.730 --> 00:33:10.720
[It kind of feels like]

00:33:10.740 --> 00:33:10.920
that counts as a Manito too.

00:33:10.920 --> 00:33:12.920
[Suddenly gets an idea about the Manito]

00:33:13.700 --> 00:33:15.280
[Go Younjung: Staff don't
usually get coffee trucks]

00:33:15.280 --> 00:33:16.860
[sent to support them, right?

00:33:17.180 --> 00:33:17.240
[Younjung thinking about gifts
for the hardworking staff]

00:33:17.240 --> 00:33:20.960
Since I can't send
a coffee truck to everyone,

00:33:21.080 --> 00:33:21.230
at least I can do this.

00:33:21.230 --> 00:33:22.860
[A comic drawn personally by Younjung]

00:33:22.860 --> 00:33:23.970
Then I wrote their names on it.

00:33:23.970 --> 00:33:24.070
We're really close.

00:33:24.070 --> 00:33:25.530
[80+ unique, heartfelt handmade gifts]

00:33:25.530 --> 00:33:27.750
I can remember everyone's name and face.

00:33:27.750 --> 00:33:29.730
[Secretly observed each person,
then drew a comic]

00:33:30.150 --> 00:33:31.530
[It was really fun back then!]

00:33:31.780 --> 00:33:33.920
[Go Younjung: Drawing a little comic
on each bread
for Myeong-soo…]

00:33:33.920 --> 00:33:36.070
[Sounds nice, right?]

00:33:36.340 --> 00:33:37.810
[The idea and the handmade gift
arrive together!]

00:33:37.810 --> 00:33:39.810
Where's the lifestyle store?

00:33:40.320 --> 00:33:40.620
Oh, it's connected.

00:33:40.620 --> 00:33:42.000
[Sudden turn]

00:33:42.430 --> 00:33:44.240
[Reading the room]

00:33:45.470 --> 00:33:47.370
[Is it here? Looks like here.]

00:33:47.510 --> 00:33:50.830
[Ah! Right~ ×3 talking to herself
while figuring out the way]

00:33:52.160 --> 00:33:53.840
[Jogging lightly]

00:33:54.850 --> 00:33:56.990
[Bread-Myeong-soo Operation]

00:33:56.990 --> 00:33:58.060
[Yongsan charcoal-grilled bakery;
Mangwon-dong scoopable scone shop;]

00:33:58.060 --> 00:33:58.590
[Mangwon-dong sea-salt bread shop]

00:33:58.590 --> 00:33:59.130
[Found the first bakery
for Bread Myungsoo Mission]

00:33:59.660 --> 00:34:03.690
[(Quick scan)]

00:34:04.210 --> 00:34:07.480
[Is this a marg—(?) Oh, it's a margarita.]

00:34:07.770 --> 00:34:08.560
Would you like it packed?

00:34:08.560 --> 00:34:10.969
[Go Younjung: Please pack it,
and I'll also take a Dubai pastry roll.]

00:34:11.080 --> 00:34:11.420
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:34:11.420 --> 00:34:13.170
[Bread Myungsoo Mission;
Yongsan charcoal bakery;]

00:34:13.170 --> 00:34:14.920
[Margarita charcoal pizza;
Dubai pastry roll]

00:34:15.370 --> 00:34:17.889
[Hehe]

00:34:18.260 --> 00:34:21.330
[Heading to the next bakery right away]

00:34:22.960 --> 00:34:25.139
[But… when did you]

00:34:25.179 --> 00:34:27.699
[teleport here?]

00:34:28.330 --> 00:34:30.870
[How did you know which route I'd take?]

00:34:30.909 --> 00:34:33.719
[Ah-ha, how did you know?]

00:34:33.739 --> 00:34:34.350
[Amazed by the camera
already being in place]

00:34:34.350 --> 00:34:36.350
Maybe I should go back the way I came.

00:34:38.750 --> 00:34:42.199
[How…]
[Her curiosity still isn't satisfied]

00:34:43.190 --> 00:34:44.440
[I have to go upstairs!]

00:34:48.449 --> 00:34:50.969
[Mom~ I'm on TV!]

00:34:51.360 --> 00:34:54.380
[Wave, wave]

00:34:54.949 --> 00:34:57.720
[Super happy]

00:34:59.460 --> 00:35:01.720
[Whoa, wow]

00:35:02.850 --> 00:35:05.630
[Wait, when did you get here?]

00:35:06.340 --> 00:35:09.880
["Teleportation director(?)"
Hard at work. Wow]

00:35:09.880 --> 00:35:10.260
Which way did you come from?

00:35:10.260 --> 00:35:12.650
[Must protect Younjung's solo shot]

00:35:18.790 --> 00:35:20.710
[Instant transmission]

00:35:21.000 --> 00:35:24.630
[(Preparing to film Younjung)]

00:35:28.170 --> 00:35:31.200
[Goosebumps] [Seriously, when...]

00:35:31.920 --> 00:35:33.670
[When did you come again!] [Haha]

00:35:34.990 --> 00:35:38.720
[Well, really… is this a superpower?]

00:35:39.260 --> 00:35:41.320
[Mission one complete!]

00:35:41.320 --> 00:35:41.910
Next,

00:35:41.910 --> 00:35:43.110
[Heading out to buy the next bread gift!]

00:35:43.110 --> 00:35:44.010
Going to Mapo.

